A very simple python interface to the tinycdb DBM library ( http://www.corpit.ru/mjt/tinycdb.html ).

Example #1 writing :

import pytinycdb

db = pytinycdb.create('foo.db')
db['foo'] = 'bar'
db['bar'] = 'baz'
print 'foo' in db # Prints True
print 'moo' in db # Prints False
db.close()

Example #2 reading :

import pytinycdb
db = pytinycdb.read('foo.db')
if 'foo' in db :
    print "Found"
    print db['foo']
else :
    print "Not found"

Thats all.

